docs.abstract: Right now, the institution of American policing lies outside any meaningful democratic control.
docs.snippet: Right now, the institution of American policing lies outside any meaningful democratic control.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2020, during the weeks of protest and civil unrest that followed the murder of George Floyd at the hands of a Minneapolis police officer, I argued that the problem of police violence and misconduct was a problem of democracy. And this week, in the wake of yet another police killing caught on camera, I think it’s worth saying, again, that the institution of American policing lies outside any meaningful democratic control.

headline.main: The Police Cannot Be a Law Unto Themselves

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The parents of Tyre Nichols, a 29-year-old Black man who died after being beaten by police officers in Memphis, will attend President Biden’s State of the Union address next week, the chairman of the Congressional Black Caucus said on Monday.

headline.main: Tyre Nichols’s Parents to Attend State of the Union Address

docs.abstract: “The Riders Come Out at Night,” by Ali Winston and Darwin BondGraham, is a case study of corruption and reform within a single police department — with implications for all of us.
docs.snippet: “The Riders Come Out at Night,” by Ali Winston and Darwin BondGraham, is a case study of corruption and reform within a single police department — with implications for all of us.
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s been more than two years since protesters filled the streets of America’s cities, since we all saw the video of a police officer’s knee on George Floyd’s neck. And yet killings at the hands of law enforcement, by various metrics, continue at a steady pace.

headline.main: What Oakland, Calif., Tells Us About Why Police Reform Is So Hard
headline.print_headline: Why Police Reform Is So Hard

docs.abstract: A Times analysis found that officers gave dozens of contradictory and unachievable orders to Mr. Nichols. The punishment was severe — and eventually fatal.
docs.snippet: A Times analysis found that officers gave dozens of contradictory and unachievable orders to Mr. Nichols. The punishment was severe — and eventually fatal.
docs.lead_paragraph: Police officers unleashed a barrage of commands that were confusing, conflicting and sometimes even impossible to obey, a Times analysis of footage from Tyre Nichols’s fatal traffic stop found. When Mr. Nichols could not comply — and even when he managed to — the officers responded with escalating force.

headline.main: 71 Commands in 13 Minutes: Officers Gave Tyre Nichols Impossible Orders
headline.print_headline: In 13 Minutes, 71 Clashing Commands and Escalating Brutality

docs.lead_paragraph: MEMPHIS — The Memphis Police Department confirmed on Monday that two additional officers had been taken off duty in connection with the death of Tyre Nichols, saying little except that the two were under investigation as city officials and prosecutors worked to determine who beyond the five officers already charged with second-degree murder should be held responsible.

docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Video images of Memphis police officers beating Tyre Nichols have drawn comparisons to shocking footage of a watershed episode more than three decades ago, in which a group of officers repeatedly struck a Black motorist as he lay on the street.

headline.main: Video images of Tyre Nichols being beaten draw comparisons to Rodney King’s beating by police officers.

docs.lead_paragraph: MEMPHIS — Tyre Nichols writhed in pain on the pavement after being beaten by Memphis police officers. His back was against a police car, his hands were cuffed and his face was bloody. He was groaning, and he kept falling over.

docs.lead_paragraph: In 2020, the city of Memphis voted to require the Memphis Police Department to enact policies designed to reduce the use of excessive force by officers. The measures came in the wake of the high-profile killings of George Floyd and Breonna Taylor by law enforcement officers.

headline.main: The Memphis police enacted reform measures in 2020.
